  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Accra Prisons Inmate Reintegration Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Discharged inmates</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project, whose main goal is to facilitate the integration of discharged prisoners back into society, is being implemented in the Awutu, Osamkrom, Ankaful, James Camp, Forifori Camp and Akuse prison camps. This project seeks to establish livestock demonstration and learning units. This project will address high HIV/AIDS rates among prisoners and recidivism among former inmates while providing alternative income sources and better nutrition in the prisons. Heifer will assist in establishing the demonstration and learning units by providing 100 sheep or goats, 100 grasscutters and cages and 1,000 chickens. Heifer will also provide training in livestock production and HIV/AIDS prevention. The Ghana prison services will be responsible for sheltering the livestock as well as daily supervision and monitoring of the prison camp projects. The Akuse prison camp came on board during this reporting period.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Training of prison Wardens in animal management. Training of Prison inmates in animal management. Provision of small ruminants and poultry to 3 prison camps.</narrative>
  </description>
